    (qid, $$B$$, $$a 1.1% sodium fluoride prescription toothpaste as the only measure$$, false, $$A 1.1% NaF prescription paste is not appropriate as the sole measure for a 4-year-old (higher ingestion risk), and the question asks for a professionally applied agent.$$, 1),
