and tongue numb)?$$, $$Accessory innervation from the mylohyoid nerve, which branches off the inferior alveolar nerve
before it enters the mandibular foramen — proximal to where the block is deposited — so it isn't
anesthetized by a standard injection and can still carry pulpal sensation to the molars.$$, $$approved$$, $$Malamed, Handbook of Local Anesthesia — accessory innervation and block failure$$, now())
