trade-off?$$, $$Silver kills cariogenic bacteria while fluoride remineralizes the lesion — together they arrest
progression non-invasively. Trade-off: the treated carious tissue permanently stains black.$$, $$approved$$, $$Wilkins, Clinical Practice of the Dental Hygienist — silver diamine fluoride$$, now())
