values ($$fc-prev-0003$$, (select id from public.taxonomy where spec_version = $$after_update_2026$$ and area = $$Provision of Clinical Dental Hygiene Services$$ and coalesce(domain, '') = $$Preventive Agents$$ and coalesce(subdomain, '') = $$Pit and fissure sealants$$), $$Why does saliva contamination of etched enamel ruin sealant retention?$$, $$Saliva coats the microporous, frosty-etched surface the resin tags need to flow into. A contaminated surface must be re-etched (or thoroughly re-dried per the product's protocol) before sealant placement, or the resin will fail to mechanically bond and the sealant will debond early.$$, $$approved$$, $$ADA/AAPD sealant guideline; Wilkins — sealant placement technique$$, now())
